33100095_1.html|title=Kerala senior citizen couple discharged after getting treated from COVID-19|author=|date=31 March 2020|website=Business Standard|language=en|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=31 March 2020}}</ref> Sixty-four more cases were reported in [[Maharashtra]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.livemint.com/news/india/mumbai-starts-containing-cluster-infections-after-reporting-64-new-cases-on-tuesday-11585665503034.html|title=Mumbai starts containing 'cluster infections' after reporting 64 new cases on Tuesday|author=|first=|date=31 March 2020|website=Livemint|language=en|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=31 March 2020}}</ref> Fifty-seven more people tested in [[Tamil Nadu]].<ref>{{Cite news|last=|first=|url=https://www.indiatoday.in/india/story/tamil-nadu-reports-57-new-covid-19-cases-in-one-day-79-attended-tablighi-jamaat-state-tally-at-124-1661904-2020-03-31|title=Tamil Nadu reports 57 new Covid-19 cases in one day, 79% attended Tablighi Jamaat. State tally at 124|date=|work=India Today|access-date=|url-status=live}}</ref> The case count in [[Delhi]] went up by twenty-three.<ref>{{Cite news|last=|first=|url=https://www.outlookindia.com/newsscroll/covid19-cases-in-delhi-rise-to-120/1786970|title=COVID-19 cases in Delhi rise to 120|date=|work=Outlook|access-date=|url-status=live}}</ref> Another twenty-one persons tested positive in [[Andhra Pradesh]].<ref>{{Cite news|last=|first=|url=https://www.thehindu.com/news/national/andhra-pradesh/positive-cases-shoot-up-to-44-in-ap/article31221648.ece|title=Among the 21 new patients, 18 are Delhi returnees and a 10-year-old boy from Anantapur|date=|work=The Hindu|access-date=|url-status=live}}</ref> Nineteen more cases were reported in [[Madhya Pradesh]] - seventeen from [[Indore]] and one each from [[Bhopal]] and [[Ujjain]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.outlookindia.com/newsscroll/19-new-coronavirus-cases-found-in-madhya-pradesh-total-66/1786739|title=19 new coronavirus 